.TH AI-EDITOR-DOCKER 1 "@VERSION@" "ai-editor-docker" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ai-editor-docker \- control AI Editor Docker container on the host
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ai-editor-docker
.I command
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ai-editor-docker
wraps systemd and \fB/usr/lib/ai-editor/docker-run.sh\fR for the AI Editor
MCP server container (HTTPS port 15000 by default).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B start
Start \fBai-editor-docker.service\fR.
.TP
.B stop
Stop the service and container.
.TP
.B restart
Restart the same container instance.
.TP
.B recreate
Remove and recreate the container (after config, certificate, or mount changes).
.TP
.B status
Show systemd and container status.
.TP
.B info
Show host paths, image tag, and container state (\fBai-editor-info\fR).
.SH PURGE
On \fBapt purge ai-editor-docker\fR, maintainer scripts stop systemd, remove the
container, remove the Docker image saved at uninstall time, and remove host log/data
directories when they contain no additional files.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /etc/default/ai-editor
Host-visible settings (port, paths, networks).
.TP
.B /etc/ai-editor/ai_editor_container.json
Service configuration bind-mounted read-only into the container.
.TP
.B /var/log/ai-editor
Application logs.
.TP
.B /var/ai-editor
Editor workspaces and version data.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ai-editor-info (1),
.BR docker (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
